name: SELF-CONFIDENCE, PT. II
description: Wow, back to serious stuff again? Already? Damn this guy must have mood swings often. How the heck is he going to hold the attention of the audience for 477 more pages? Annnnd transition to self-confidence. Welcome back to normally scheduled broadcast of low self-esteem and when your confidence level plummets. What are we so scared of? As previously mentioned, sometimes our lizard brains have this ironclad grip on our psyche. Fear is what keeps you up at night. Fear is being a failure. Fear is dying alone. Fear can even be what keeps you from writing the next word in this very sentence that lots of potentially important people are going to read that can either make or break your career one day. That being said, we can't let fear rule our lives. Fear are like bumpers on cars, sometimes you can't see when you're backing up to park and the wall kindly tells you you just hit it. (BREAKING NEWS) Wait...what's that all modern cars now have backup cameras preinstalled? Oh for F's sake, well there goes my analogy. You know what I'm getting at. Fear helps keep us alive, but don't let it kill you.
